# Repost-with-agent v3.0.0 environment variables.
#
# v3 has NO API SDKs and NO Playwright. The agent drives the user's logged-in
# browser via its own browser MCP. The only env vars that matter are the data
# dir override (rarely useful) and the Telegram notify fallback (preferred path
# is `repost-with-agent notify configure`).
#
# Compare to the v2.6.0 .env.example — the X / LinkedIn / Facebook / Playwright
# variables are gone. v2 → v3 migration: see docs/migration-v2-to-v3.md.

# Override the runtime data dir (defaults to ~/.repost-with-agent).
# Either env var name works; the short form takes precedence.
# REPOST_DATA_DIR=
# REPOST_WITH_AGENT_DATA_DIR=

# Telegram-on-publish notifier (NON-NEGOTIABLE before any live run).
# Preferred path: `repost-with-agent notify configure --bot-token <T> --chat-id <C> --test`
# (writes ~/.repost-with-agent/notify.json with mode 0600).
# Env vars below are a fallback for CI / cron environments. Both must be set
# for the env source to be used.
# REPOST_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
# REPOST_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=
